<br>
I was grouped in Highpass, at the gnoll ledge. There were 4 of us there: 2 melees, a caster, and myself.  Our timing had gotten off, and we ended up way over our heads due to repops.  Epsecially when the main tank went LD.<br>
<br>
I started chain healing on the remaining melee, and of course got aggro.  I didn't last too long, I'm afraid, but I spent all my mana on Heals.<br>
<br>
I respawn at my bind point, in front of High Keep.  Amazingly, my groupmates are still alive, but dropping.  I mem my healing spell (only) and run back over.  Two gnolls are left, and the caster in the group is OOM and using his dagger.  I get there right before the melee drops and start healing him.<br>
<br>
We were too stubborn, I guess, and should have run when the main tank went LD... but somehow we managed to pull it off with just me dying... and if I hadn't have died, we wouldn't have pulled it off because I had no mana. <p>Kimbera [Aquilo di Arcis] 50 human cleric <BR>
