ody....sigh. Can't summon....Back to the top, summon.....too far. Sigh....petition. GM says body is accessible, grrr. Mind you, at this time I was in uber full leather armor, I needed my body back <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Finally after about 1.5 hours, found a friendly druid to lev me and literally dropped down the side of the cliff hitting my summon corpse key constantly. Found it about midway down the cliff, drifted on down dragging my bod all the way. We did eventually make it to Qeynos with only a few close calls, but took all night instead of the hour we thought it would <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  The really ironic thing is after poking around the Qeynos area and checking out Blackburrow (dieing there several times ), we decided that Freeport area was better and ran back....lol.<br>
