<br>
I remember Arlan leveling very quickly too hehe.  Indeed he was a gifted Monk of great skill.  He first joined Ashoc, and was an integral member of that family for a long time.  Most of his upper 30s through mid 40s development was spent with that family.  When Triton formed, he ended up going there with most of his Ashoc friends.  He and I have stayed in touch all this time, and I know that he is well.  He has recently graduated from college, so I imagine he is still job hunting hehe.<br>
<br>
The first Monk on Povar to acquire the feign death skill however, was neither Arlan nor myself hehe.  It was Wiktor.  I remember seeing Wiktor practicing feign death all over Blackburrow.  I used to crack up laughing at him falling over pretending to die so often hehe.  I obtained my 17th degree a few days later, as did Arlan hehe.  I remember the 3 of us having a laughing fit over my discovery that feign could be practiced over and over while still lying down hehe.  Thus preventing everyone around you from having to listen to it over &amp; over &amp; over again LOL.  Poor Wiktor hadn't known it could still be trained that way heehee.<br>
<br>
He and Arlan then went on to level with great speed, since that was part of what brought them each joy from the game.  I, of course, cared little for such things hehe.  So I leveled at my own pace, and made my way here and there.  Never once did I lose touch with Brother Arlan.  He was always very kind to me and never forgot the lessons I taught early on.  We shared much, he and I, in the way of technique and strategy.<br>
