<br>
I am very proud to say I was a Fireblade Sir Splos. Most of those fireblades are in my guild currently, though sadly FU has taken many as well. <br>
<br>
From my 27th level, I  stayed at HK (on waiting lists for a group-often for hours) until my 37th level due to its ease and relative safety. At around my 38th level, I discovered that the trolls in lake rathe were fantastic exp and fantastic loot (200pp a night) for a person as poor as myself. I stayed at those boring trolls grouped all the time. By around my 46th season I soloed at the trolls. Prior to my soloing, I met Cammus, a Brazillian Enchanter Erudite. I also met his wonderful Druid wife, Graycie.  Cammus told me how exicited he was of being in Aquilo. He urged me to apply. I did apply and was accepted to Aquilo Ferox. I was still a noob when I joined Aquilo despite being 53d level. No wait, I still am!<br>
<br>
I stayed in Aquilo Ferox, after Ookies' disbanding, after the server split. I served in it as an officer. Later if became Aquilo Phoenix. Then Aquilo of course merged with Arcis (heavily Fireblades too-Aarnwulf, Storrme , Slarena, Ceten, Lenoin, Kiisk, Tristansebast, Uasu-perhaps others) and AdA was born. But many of the former Arcis left and went to Forces Unknown. <br>
<br>
Well then now Im Unleashed, with the same family spirit I once enjoyed in Aquilo. I sure hope that AdA has this family spirit. From what I hear they do and its good to hear. <br>
<br>
With Raidon joining, we have a large chuck of our old Fireblades, aside from the ones FU has taken /sigh. We also brought in Stormwatch folks (goodfolks) and of course the Wolf Hounds (were always close to fireblades and OTW) and a few others to form a new family. In spite of this, we remember many members of AdA fondly. This is also the reason some of us, like myself,  keep coming here. <br>
<br>
One lost Fireblade is Tynadinia who is now GL of a new small guild. Another lost one is Portree /sigh I dont know where she has gone.  <p><HTML>
