<br>
I'll never forget the night I took on my sister Danodare's persona.  I had been helping her with Fear and was trying to help her get some Shiverback items.  She camped her character just outside the portal so I could log her on if appropriate.  I remember logging her on and spending the next 15 minutes feigning death over and over and over again LOL.  People in the Grey Council family kept asking what the heck was wrong with her heehee.  I revealed to them that it was me in a much more alluring form hehe.  Then they all understood that I had been captured by the irresistible female feign death bug HAH.<br>
<br>
Lady Noitide, what an interesting story to be sure.  I have many fond memories of the Fireblades family.  Those who moved on to populate even larger families also came to be near and dear to my heart.  My associations with the Aquilo and Arcis people are well documented, but I also had significant interactions with the last 2 you mentioned.<br>
<br>
I remember Lady Tynadinia well.  She was a prominent member of the Triton family for a long time.  I remember helping her obtain her Epic in that zone where all the big golem types were hehe.  I also remember older days when we fought side by side in Fear together.  It was rather new back then and was one of only 2 planes hehe.<br>
<br>
Lady Portree, however, I must say I have had the longest attachment to.  I have known the gentle lady of magic longer than almost any other who now resides in any of the families you mentioned.  When many of you were not yet even born, much less of great capability hehe, Lady Portree and I roamed the Rathe Mountains together.  She was always granting my poor human eyes the advantaged sight of a coldstone.  This was well before the many options of various masks were available to those like myself.<br>
<br>
Indeed, the kind and beautiful Portree I consider to be one of my oldest and dearest friends.  We have so many fond memories of adventuring together in days long ago that it brings a tear to my eye.  Noitide you shall be happy to know that Portree is quite well.  I spoke to her not even a week ago.<br>
<br>
In fact, she has rejoined that ancient family so populated long ago by many of you who come here still.  Fireblades once again hosts the magical lady and she is surrounded by old and dear friends.  She left Aquilo with little notice in late December, and thought it best to do so since her role was uncertain.  She seems quite happy and fond of her times spent with those who have moved on <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  I will never forget her, and I could tell countless stories of our adventures in the lower 30s threshhold hehe.<br>
<br>
